name: Galway City Museum
description: Galway City Museum is a famous museum in Galway City. The renowned museum was established on 29th July 2006 and is based alongside the Spanish Arch. The official website for the museum was instituted on 27th November 2008. The building was assembled in the mid-1970s. Originally the Galway City Museum is situated in Comerford House beforehand artist Clare Sheridan had resided there. The museum commenced as a remaining contribution of medieval stones that was acquired by Clare Sheridan.

name: Galway Cathedral
description: The Galway Cathedral was previously known as the Cathedral of Our Lady Assumed into Heaven and St Nicholas. The Galway Cathedral is based on the banks of the Corrib River; which was the initial location of the ancient city prison. Builders commenced the construction of the cathedral in 1958 and the construction reached its conclusion in 1965; the aim was to ensure that this was the utmost glorious stone cathedral built in Europe.

name: National Aquarium Galway
description: The Natural Aquarium is situated in Salthill alongside the picturesque Galway Bay and the world prominent "Promenade Walk". The Natural Aquarium of Ireland(Galway Atlantaquara) is designed to demonstrate the medley of marine species from all over Ireland. The establishment hosts hundreds of marine creatures obtained from Ireland's rivers, shores and oceans. The premises contains two floors of expositions that delineate the maritime history of Galway.

name: Oranmore Castle
description: Oranmore Castle was established in the 15th Century. Oranmore Castle was the Clanricardes' fortress; the Clanricardes were a distinguished Norman family who resided in Galway. Galway was immersed in the overlordship of the Marquess and the fifth Earl Clanricarde. In March 1642, the town rebelled with the aim to unite the Confederates with St Augustin's Fort. A vigorous garrison was arranged in Oranmore Castle by Clanricarde where the Fort of Galway was provisioned from the sea until 1643.

name: Open The Door Galway
description: Open The Door Escape Room provides people a captivating and unorthodox strategy as a technique to spend free time with companions.
